<h2>Chris J. Maddison â Prospective Trainees</h2>
      <p>I am always looking for exceptional people to join our group. Please read below to see how I recruit for the position you're interested in. Unfortunately, I can't respond directly to every request for supervision.<p>
			<p><b>Prospective graduate students.</b> I recruit PhD and MSc students once a year through the <a href="https://web.cs.toronto.edu/graduate/prospective">Department of Computer Science</a>. I can't respond to all off-cycle requests, so please apply in the fall when applications open.</p>
      <p><b>Prospective undergraduate students.</b> I only recruit undergraduate students sporadically. These positions typically involve working closely with one of my graduate students, so a strong mutual fit is essential. I can't respond to all requests, so I recommend reaching out directly to my current group members whose research appeals to you.</p>
      <p><b>Prospective postdoctoral fellows.</b> I recruit postdocs throughout the year through a number of programs, primarily through the <a href="https://vectorinstitute.ai/">Vector Institute</a>. Please reach out <a href="mailto:cmaddis@cs.toronto.edu">via email</a> to discuss.</p>
